<div id="about"><div id="wrapper-about"><div id="about-everything"><div id="i-wave"></div><div id="ccode1"><div id="about-header"><div id="header-grid"><h2>know us</h2></div><div id="header-brief-grid2"><p>We help people develop skills and their ability to use their own social resources to enhance their individual and collective well-being of communities and solve many social problems.</p></div></div><div id="about-container"> <div id="about-container-floats"><div id="rt"> <div id="actr"><div id="txt"><h2>Adventures Fill Us</h2> <p>We are a bunch of buds who live in a fancy of sentiments. We are working with volunteers and love creating awesome and real connections.</p><p>We also enjoy good food, sound sleeps, great friends, memorable smiles and a working sense of possibilities + exploring convictions. </p><h3>We Do Good Stuff.</h3></div><div id="pic"><img src="images/adventures-taj.jpg"></div></div></div></div><div id="about-container-floats"><div id="fl"> <div id="actl"><div id="pic"><img src="images/floods2.jpg"></div><div id="txt"><h2>Things Moved Us</h2> <p>This project was started with the help of - <a>Feeding India</a>.</p><p>The developers were once trapped in floods and human nature confused them.</p><p>Humans are brave enough to help each-other out in certain conditions, then why is there still poverty in our country? Maybe, they can't see the dimensions of this calamity.</p><p>We mostly collect things you don't need and help you use them as an element of transformation.</p><p>The cure lies in time and we desire to see that time. </p><h3>We Enjoy Little Things.</h3></div></div></div></div></div><div id="icode2"><hr class="style1"/><div id="about-container-floats" style="padding-top:0px;"><div id="count-box-wrap"><div id="count-box"><div id="pre-count"><h2>Our teams operate currently</h2></div><div id="count-to"><div id="box-pre"><h3>in</h3></div><div id="box-mid"><h1><b class="timer" id="loca" data-from="0" data-to="23" data-speed="2000"></b></h1></div><div id="box-next"><h3>localities</h3></div></div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<div id="count-to"><div id="box-pre"><h3>with</h3></div><div id="box-mid"><h1><b class="timer" id="volunt" data-from="0" data-to="168" data-speed="3000"></b></h1></div><div id="box-next"><h3>volunteers</h3></div></div></div></div></div><div style="clear:both;"></div><hr class="style2"/><div id="about-container-floats" class="bx-fix-padding"><div id="thoughts-container"><div id="thoughts-wrap"><ul class="bxslider"><li><div id="thought-box"><div id="thought-author"><img class="flip" src="images/Coco-Chanel.png" alt="?"></div><div id="thought-details"><p id="details-author">Coco Chanel<br><span> - French fashion designer</span></p><blockquote><p> Some people think luxury is the opposite of poverty. It is not. It is the opposite of vulgarity.</p></blockquote></div></div></li><li><div id="thought-box"><div id="thought-author"><img class="flip" src="images/Bill-Gates.png" alt="?"></div><div id="thought-details"><p id="details-author">Bill Gates <br><span> - Business magnate and philanthropist</span></p><blockquote><p> I believe that if you show people the problems and you show them the solutions they will be moved to act.</p></blockquote></div></div></li><li><div id="thought-box"><div id="thought-author"><img class="flip" src="images/Edmund-Burke.png" alt="?"></div><div id="thought-details"><p id="details-author"> Edmund Burke<br><span> - Author and philosopher</span></p><blockquote><p> The only thing necessary for the triumph of evil is for good people to do nothing.</p></blockquote></div></div></li><li><div id="thought-box"><div id="thought-author"><img class="flip" src="images/Martin-Luther-King-Jr.png" alt="?"></div><div id="thought-details"><p id="details-author">Martin Luther King, Jr.<br><span> - Baptist minister and civil rights activist</span></p><blockquote><p>Our lives begin to end the day we become silent about things that matter.</p></blockquote></div></div></li><li><div id="thought-box"><div id="thought-author"><img class="flip" src="images/Buchman-Frank.png" alt="?"></div><div id="thought-details"><p id="details-author">Frank Buchman<br><span> - Protestant evangelist </span></p><blockquote><p> There is enough in the world for everyone's need, but not for everyone's greed.</p></blockquote></div></div></li><li><div id="thought-box"><div id="thought-author"><img class="flip" src="images/Nelson-Mandela.png" alt="?"></div><div id="thought-details"><p id="details-author">Nelson Mandela<br><span> - Former President of South Africa</span></p><blockquote><p> As long as poverty, injustice and gross inequality exist in our world, none of us can truly rest. </p></blockquote></div></div></li></ul></div></div></div><img src="images/arrow-down.png" style="margin-bottom:-7px;"> </div></div></div></div></div>